Task 2: Customer Segmentation Using K-Means

🎯 Objective
Cluster customers based on spending habits and propose marketing strategies for each group.

📂 Dataset
  - Source: Mall Customers Dataset
  - Features: CustomerID, Gender, Age, Annual Income, Spending Score

🛠️ Steps Performed
  1. Data Cleaning & EDA  
  2. K-Means Clustering applied (optimal clusters selected using Elbow Method)  
  3. PCA used for dimensionality reduction & visualization  
  4. Identified 4 customer segments:
     - High Income, High Spending  
     - High Income, Low Spending  
     - Low Income, High Spending  
     - Low Income, Low Spending  

📊 Results
  - Segments visualized with PCA scatter plot  
  - Marketing strategies proposed for each group  

🚀 Skills Gained
  - Unsupervised learning (K-Means)  
  - Dimensionality reduction (PCA)  
  - Customer segmentation  
  - Data-driven strategy development
